@sthar: Why vote me or you?  Do you think we are the best lynch targets or you just what?  If you are going off of who has the most votes then there are two people tied with me at this time so that doesn't make much sense.  Also, you could always try giving us some valuable information if you think all that we have now is invaluable.<br>
<br>
If anyone has any questions for me fire away.  I will be more than happy to oblige your questions.

sthar8 Paper responded.  Now it is time for you to explain yourself.  I can't wait to see this.<br>
<br>
@Don: what is your opinion on sthar8?

@notreallygood<br>
Besides this site, how experienced with playing mafia are you?<br>
<br>
@beastcharizard<br>
Would you mind elaborating on your scum read on don_johnston?<br>
<br>
@don_johnston<br>
Give me one of your initial town read and initial scum read.

@Elyse's super wall: I am just a weird person.  I asked Titus to answer the questions so they had a good transition into the game and they would be following suit on what most everyone else had done.  I would like to say not all of those questions were useless to me.  Sthar8 used the who did you play with one to do a Meta check.  You know, I get the: "he is trying to act pro-town" thing every single game I play.  I am not sure if people think I am always scum or if it is scum trying to get my lynched.  It never crosses people's mind that I might actually be town doing pro-town things.  My comments on Sthar's play didn't come out of nowhere.  He asked in a previous post for people to give their opinion on it so I did.  Now what had changed was they were not posting any better so i decided that they were the greatest threat to the town and that probably was not going to change no matter what they did.  Finally, I think all my posts are going to be "awkward", just so you know.<br>
<br>
@Titus: Your vote on Don looks like pure OMGUS because of the line: "This vote is utter bullshit."<br>
<br>
@Elyse: Titus has a grand total of 7 posts but yet he is a town read.  Please explain this to me since I fail to see how you can get a read off 7 posts(was like 5 or 6 when you got your read) but not 11 posts from Don.

@Runnerman, that is essentially a wifom defense. Scum wouldn't do it and I'm town so you must be wrong.<br>
<br>
To me, it seems like a possible scum play, especially with newer players. You know that voting your FoSer would get the person in trouble, so the votes cross.

@Beast, I agree. I hate policy lynching.<br>
<br>
@TSO, That being said. I'd like you to turn your attention away from strh8. What are your other reads?<br>
<br>
@All, I'm beginning to form a town read on Smudger. He hasn't posted a lot but his posts are generally protown imo.

Also happy birthday don?<br>
<br>
@TSO- if you insist on acting like a caricature, I'm going to start treating you like one.

@Titus: I never discredited your vote.  All I said is that it made it look like OMGUS. Prefacing a vote with anything along lose lines makes something seem like pure emotion and no reasoning.  You had reasoning and I am not trying to say you didn't have reasoning.  I said "looked like OMGUS" not "it is OMGUS".  They are two different things in my opinion.<br>
<br>
The bold part is me being frustrated.  I hate people thinking me acting like town, in my mind, is me being scummy.  I play pro-town as scum but it sucks when I am village and get voted out d1 because of it.  I tried switching up how I played once and got policy lynched d1 as well.

@Grim: You really think TSO is the best lynch today?<br>
<br>
I will post my case against runnerman later today when I have more time.   I don't just vote people for no reason.

Arguments between two people have been the most annoying thing this game.  Can we please stop it?  Communicating is fine and talking to each other is fine but don't spam the thread.<br>
<br>
@DJ: why do you only ask Titus questions?<br>
<br>
@Titus: What is your take on DJ?
